 *** DEFINITION OF SYMBOLS ***
 FRAME#   = running number of the data image
 SCALE    = SCALING FACTOR FOR THIS DATA IMAGE
 BACKGND  = MEAN BACKGROUND IN AN IMAGE PIXEL FOR THIS IMAGE
  GAIN    = MEAN OF THE GAIN-VALUES ON DATA IMAGE
            "GAIN" RELATES POISSON-DISTRIBUTED X-RAY COUNTS
            TO DATA IMAGE PIXEL VALUES SUCH THAT
            GAIN * X-RAY_COUNTS = PIXEL_VALUE - DARK CURRENT
 #PIXEL   = NUMBER OF SAMPLING POINTS ON DATA IMAGE USED
            FOR DETERMINATION OF GAIN & BACKGROUND.
            <0 SPECIFIES AN ERROR CODE AFTER ACCESSING IMAGE
            -1: CANNOT OPEN OR READ IMAGE FILE
            -3: WRONG DATA FORMAT

